{
  "stem": "323.1",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 100,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And somehow-- I really didn't mind going.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 100,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Because I was sick and tired of staying where the-- I had no one to play with, I had no one there.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 100,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I was-- I couldn't do anything anymore.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 100,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And people used to point fingers at us, there go the Jews because we had to wear the stupid star.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 100,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And it just-- I thought, gee, maybe I'll be together with other Jews.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 100,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I mean, I was a child.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 100,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I didn't know what-- we did not know what a concentration camp was.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 101,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Some I knew and some I didn't.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I felt terrible.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Like some said, oh, she doesn't look like a Jew at all.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Like you know, like the-- some people think Jews have horns or something like that.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then sometimes people were sympathetic, like, I mean, we were small children, [BACKGROUND NOISE] so.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But it just-- it's just life changed so drastically.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There was-- it was much better than life in the camps, but I didn't know that at the time.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But it was just wasn't-- it was not so nice living there anymore.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And people who were your friends two years ago became your arch enemies and didn't want to have anything to do with you anymore.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the ones that still would have wanted to be your friends were afraid to do so, because it would be at the risk of their own lives.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then I saw the Hitler youth marching.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I remember we had a parade because Hitler was supposed to come.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they sang this song in German.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
